text.section:
To the extent reasonably possible, an individual who makes a report under this section shall include in the report the following information:
the name, age, and home address of the child;
the name and home address of the child's parent or other person who is responsible for the child's care;
the whereabouts of the child;
the nature and extent of the substantial risk of sexual abuse of the child, including any evidence or information available to the reporter concerning possible previous instances of sexual abuse; and
any other information that would help to determine:
the cause of the substantial risk of sexual abuse; and
the identity of any individual responsible for the substantial risk of sexual abuse.
